    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="uva_jc.00414_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1872-12-16">Dec. 16, '72.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Mr. Otis,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I mail you, same mail with this, two copies of the little Volume, "<hi
                    rend="underline">As a Strong Bird</hi>" &amp;c.&#8212;the only form in which I
                have the Dartmouth College poem.<ptr target="loc.02862_n2"/></p>
            <p>The price of the two is &#36;1.50cts.</p>
            <p>"<hi rend="underline">Democratic Vistas</hi>"<ptr target="n4122"/> is printed in a
                little book by itself. price 75cts.</p>
            <p>There is not, (&amp; <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="uva_jc.00415_large.jpg" type="verso"
                /> probably will not be) any later or different edition of "<hi rend="underline"
                    >Leaves of Grass</hi>" than the one I forwarded you last spring.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
                <address>
                    <addrLine>Solicitors Office Treasury</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>Washington</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>D. C.</addrLine>
                </address>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="uva_jc.00416_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="uva_jc.00417_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text> 
